Often there can be seen on the streets of Malvern one of two local dancing groups.
A ladies side,{OLD MEG,}in their white dresses with red over skirts and clogged feet, can be seen performing dances of the{North Western Clog} tradition.
Dances with a more local flavour can be seen being performed by the{ {SILURIAN BORDER MORRISMEN.}This side, with their blackened faces, black bowler hats,bells and be-ribboned white shirts are the leading exponents of the{Welsh Border Morris}tradition. All of their dances have been collected from local villages and towns and at Christmas time can also be seen performing a local{Mummers {Play.}
